The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation at a Glance

 Schoolgirls run over by train

 Hajipur (PTI): Two schoolgirls were run over by the Raxaul-Hajipur Intercity Express while they were trying to cross the tracks near the Ghoswar halt on the Hajipur-Muzaffarpur section in Bihars Vaishali district on Saturday. They were on their way to school.

 Railway sources said seven-year-old Muskan and eight-year-old Priti were crossing the tracks at an unmanned level crossing under Sonepur division of the East Central Railway when they were hit by the train. Both died on the spot.

 The accident sparked a rail blockade by local residents. Agitated villagers blocked the tracks at Ghoswar, disrupting rail traffic between Hajipur and Muzaffarpur stations for over an hour. They shouted slogans against the railway administration and demanded compensation, the sources said.

 Injured actor in hospital

 Mumbai (PTI): Sanjana Srivastava, a model 

 and TV actor, was admitted to a private hospital with head 

 injuries on Saturday.

 She was brought to the Suburban Arogya Nidhi hospital in an unconscious condition by unidentified persons and was in coma, police said.

 The police suspect Sanjana, who is from Lucknow, was assaulted and suffered head injuries in the attack. They are questioning the persons who brought her to the hospital.

 Juhu police have registered a case of assault and were probing the cause of her injuries, the police added.

 Rapist jailed

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A man has been 

 sent to jail for 10 years and slapped a fine of Rs 10,000 

 for raping a 15-year-old neighbour in September 2004.

 Additional district sessions judge K.K. Asthana sentenced Devi Singh, of Machroli village in the district, for raping the girl in a nearby field.

 Bribe arrest

 New Delhi (PTI): The Central Bureau 

 of Investigation on Saturday arrested an officer of the 

 railways engineering services while he was allegedly accepting 

 a bribe of Rs 20,000 to clear a contractors bill. 

 Pradeep Kumar Sharma, chief inspector of works in Pathankot, 

 had demanded the bribe to clear a bill of 2.25 lakh, the 

 CBI said.

 Bail refused

 New Delhi (PTI): A Delhi court has refused 

 bail to an Israeli accused of drug trafficking and laundering 

 money worth 10 million euros, equivalent to Rs 50 crore.

 More 

 than 3,600 students from a Chennai-based school demonstrated 

 their skills in Hatha Yoga on Saturday. The students 

 performed 31 different postures for about an hour.




